### Business logic

New set of components provide this basic workflow:

1. input or scan a barcode
2. barcode looked up (existing API) and the type of scanned object is inferred
3. component behavior branches:
   a. non-fungible item (serialized) - jump to location input
   b. package item - option to 'unpack' - select only partial quantity to move (removed quantity becomes fungible)
   c. batch item / fungible item - specify quantity + specify current location
4. location input or scanned confirms the transaction (add visible disclaimer that it's going to happen)
5. if response OK - close the dialog
6. if response NOK - keep dialog open and show detailed reason why movement is not possible (provided by the backend)

Provide 2 sets of componets, one for barcode readers and one for desktop. Use the global switch `scannerMode` from `use-app-settings.ts` to switch which one to show.

1. barcode: no dropdowns simple auto-focusable inputs, use correct input types (e.g. for numbers/amounts). Keep the barcode workflow in mind - ultimate goal is zero clicking around if possible. Use <q-form>'s ability to seamlesly transfer focus from input to input

2. desktop: no reader available, replace all inputs where it's possible with dropdown selecs (all should be available under `src/components/selects`). Add a missing one if needed (as to always be self-contained)

### API / Interface contract

- new endpoint specified bellow part of the /warehouse API
- HTTP POST `/warehouse/movement`
- movement params part of the request body

